HEADWORD: Zauschneria
<hw>Zau*schne"ri*a</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., named
for <person>M. <etsep>Zauschner</etsep></person>, a Bohemian
botanist.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A genus of flowering plants.
<spn>Zauschneria Californica</spn> is a suffrutescent perennial, with
showy red flowers much resembling those of the garden fuchsia.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

